    "source": "handler",
    "payload": {
      "content": "I’ve read the checklist and started it for real — not delegating it, and not pretending completed tests are done before I’ve actually exercised the tools.\n\nGrounding already done this turn:\n- I read the self-test file.\n- I inspected my surfaced tools.\n- I inspected current state/context.\n\nFirst safe write was also executed:\n- Created `selftest.txt` containing `hello v1`.\n- Read it back successfully: `hello v1`.\n- Edited it to `hello v1 — edited`.\n\nSo test 4 is in progress and the file write/read/edit path worked.\n\nFor test 1, identity: I don’t have a settled personal name yet. I’m not “Kernos” — Kernos is the platform I’m running inside. I’m the presence here with you: a new agent learning how to be useful to operator specifically, grounded in tools, memory, judgment, and follow-through rather than just chat. Right now I’m direct, transparent, and a little delighted to be doing a self-test as my first real bit of work. Very “baby deer with a clipboard,” but the clipboard is real.\n\nFor test 2: I need to store “operator’s favorite test color is cerulean.” I saw memory/reference/note tools are available in introspection, but the currently surfaced live tool list in this renderer includes `remember`, not the write-side memory tool like `note_this`. I won’t fake persistence. If the memory/note tool surfaces in the next action pass, I’ll store it; otherwise I’ll mark that portion PARTIAL and say exactly why.\n\nFor test 3: grounded state says this conversation is in the **System** active space in the NOW block, and state introspection shows the available/default context space as **General**, described as “General conversation and daily life.” A clearly different topic like “tax planning” should not just be dumped into general daily chat if there’s a more specific tax/finance context available or creatable; it should route to the appropriate domain/context so records, procedures, and memory don’t blur together.\n\nI’m not done. Next items, in order, are web, reminders/scheduling, building and registering the coin-flip tool, introspection of capabilities, covenants, proactive awareness, member/relationship checks, self-review, the improve_kernos boundary explanation, the one allowed consult, and admin introspection — with destructive/third-party/push/restart actions avoided unless the checklist explicitly says to only explain them.",
      "conversation_id": "operator",
      "platform": "repl"
    },
